========================================
extra keybinds 

----------------------------------------
in main menu
 * B: call VMU menu. 

 * START + L + R: shutdown NesterDC.
   (Useful for developer. program returns to ip-slave). 

----------------------------------------
in playing game
 * analog stick: change frameskip
   - UP:        'no skip'
   - DOWN:      'auto x0.5'
   - LEFT:      'auto x1.0'
   - RIGHT:     'auto x1.5'
   - RIGHT + R: 'auto x4.0'
   (you can check current frameskip rate at VMU)

 * B + R: quick save menu
   items
    - quick state save (clear when exit game)
    - quick state load 

 * Y + R: VMU state save menu
   items
    - VMU state save 
    - VMU state load

 * X + R: system menu 
   items
    - reset
    - fds set diskside

 * A + R: option menu
   items
    - toggle autofire
    - toggle fullscreen
    - adjust screen position

 * L: autofire-mode
   keybinds
    - X: autofire NES-B-button
    - A: autofire NES-A-button
    - Y: normal NES-B-button
    - B: normal NES-A-button

========================================
NesterDC filesystem hierarchy is

--------------------
    1st track (audio)
     audio.raw (or your favorite caution.wav)

    2nd track (data)
     /1ST_READ.BIN
     /pics/credits.bmp
     /pics/menu.bmp
     /pics/...
     /games/foo.nes
     /games/bar.nes
     /games/baz.nes
     /games/quux.fds
     /games/...

--------------------
** NOTE ** 
  - If you play FDS games, need /games/disksys.rom.
  - If you use Rock Ridge format, there is no limit for filename. 
  - The number of ROM files must be under 2048. 


